@NODE 1.2. "Contents"


SMB-Connect V1.05 contains 2 programs;

@{"SMB-Handler" Link 2.} V0.20
@{"SMB-Net" Link 3.}     V0.12

Please accept that both programs are BETA-versions!!!

@ENDNODE

@NODE 1.3. "Requierements"

- Kickstart  2.04+
- TCP-stack (bsdsocket  V3.0+) [Miami,AmiTCP,Genesis]
- to input any passwords reqtools.library V38+
- for parsing of networks  MUI V3.8+ (muimaster.library V8+)

If you like to connect to a printer you must have the amiga
printer device.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 1.4. "Security"


There is  no  security  to  protect  your  passwords  in  the
mountlist. The passwords in SMB-Net are coded, but not with a
high security level. All passwords were uncoded transmit over
the network.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "SMB-Handler"

This program make the connection to the net device. It can be
used without SMB-Net.


@{" Installation SMB-Handler " Link 2.1.}
@{" Mountlist " Link 2.2.}
@{" Printer " Link 2.3.}
@{" Errors SMB-Handler " Link 2.4.}
@{" Todo (SMB-Handler) " Link 2.5.}
@{" History SMB-Handler " Link 2.6.}
@ENDNODE

@NODE 2.1. "Installation SMB-Handler"


Copy the file smb-handler to L: and the laguages files to
locale:catalogs/<language>.

You can also use the installer-script.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2.2. "Mountlist"


Here some examples for a SMB-Handler mountlist entry.

   /* net drive handler */
   Handler     = L:SMB-Handler
   Stacksize   = 40000
   Priority    = 10
   GlobVec     = -1
   Mount       = 1
   Startup     = "C=\\\\DEVELOPER\\D MH=AMIGA W=BECMARINE U=Micha P=xxxx DN=DEV_D"

   /* LPT1 printer handler */
   Handler     = L:SMB-Handler
   Stacksize   = 40000
   Priority    = 10
   GlobVec     = -1
   Mount       = 1
   Startup     = "C=\\\\PRINTSERVER\\HP500 U=Micha P='' PRINTER BP GFX"

If you have any words with a space char you must this field set in ''.

The statup tooltypes:

C       computername und sharename
	\\\\computer\\share
	all computernames you can write as name:ip-address.
	p.e. "\\\\AMIGA2000:192.168.1.31\\share"

MH      your hostname, p.e localhost:127.0.0.1

W       name of workgroup ore domain

U       username

P       uncoded password (see @{"Security" Link 1.4.});

DN      the volume name for the device (shown on the workbench).
	if you not have this entry the name will be "<share> on <computer>".

QUIET   no error requesters;

PRINTER the share name is an printer

BP      (PRINTER only)
	BusyPointer, while sending print data over the network the
	mousepointer will set to the clock.

GFX     (PRINTER only)
	Printing in graphics mode, not sending eol or eot

PM      for special test loggins you can set this value to 2 (PM=2).

LOG     for errors while loggin you can set this value to 255 to create
	a logfile with all importent data.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 2.3. "Printer"

For using the printer correctly you must redirect the printer
output with the cmd command.

mount lpt1:
run <NIL: >NIL: c:cmd parallel LPT1: opt m

@{"SMB-Net" Link 3.} make this for you.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2.4. "Errors SMB-Handler"

This are a list with errors of SMB-Handlers:

errortext ....(run TCP/IP)?
---------------------------

One  of  the  given  computernames  can  not  resolved  to  a
ip-address.  All  names  must have an entry in the etc:hosts!
You can input the  ip-address  direct  after  the  name  with
trailing ':' p.e. AMIGA2000:192.168.1.31

Generaly you must can  successfull  ping  from  computer1  to
computer2  and  computer2  to  computer1. If you have try the
connection with samba smbclient and works and smb-handler  do
not  work  then the reason is that smbclient send a broadcast
to get the ip-address and SMB-Handler not do that.


Problems while connection
-------------------------

SMB-Handler sends uncoded passwords. Some systems not  accept
this.  If  you  connect  to Windows NT V4.0 ServicePack 3 and
higher, please read the docs of ServicePack 3.

Try passwords in uppercase! Try sharename in uppercase!


not implemented filesystem commands
-----------------------------------

NOTIFICATIONS, EXALL


long filenames
--------------

Filename longer than 108 bytes are not supported.


error in filedate
-----------------

If computers are located in different timezones the date is corrupt.

@ENDNODE

