@NODE 3.1. "Installation SMB-Net"


Copy the file smb-net and the icon to any directory and  copy
the languagefiles to locale:catalogs/<language>.

You can also use the installer-script.

SMB-Net requieres @{"SMB-Handler" Link 2.} im L:-directory.
The mount command must located in C:.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 3.2. "Tooltypes"


APPXPOS         x-position of Application-Icons;

APPYPOS         y-position of Application-Icons;

APPPARSE        ON|OFF oder TRUE|FALSE
		searching while startup for connection open with
		smb-handler at this time. Turn of this after first start.

FONT            name of the font for mainwindow;

FONTSIZE        size of the font for mainwindow;

CMD             name of using cmd-commands (default: sys:utilities/cmd)

LOGINLOG        =255, give the SMB-Handler this value to the LOG tooltype;

DOMAIN          names of domain and the masterbrowser or domaincontroller
		for parsing:
		DOMAIN=DOM_1=DOM_1CONTROLL;DOM_2=DOM_2CONTROLL

MASTERBROWSER   If you only connet to one domain or workgroup you can give
		the name of your masterbrowser.

If give DOMAIN and MASTERBROWSER, DOMAIN will be used.
benutzt.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 3.3. "Commandline"


To use the cli-part of SMB-Net the workbench part must be already started.

D=DIE/S         close the connection to <device>;
M=MOUNT/S       open the connection to <device>;
DEV=DEVICE      devicename, defined in SMB-Net without ':'!!!
Q=QUIT/S        close smb-net

@ENDNODE

@NODE 3.4. "Errors SMB-Net"


Sone enfocer-hits will detect, but it works.

There are no error messages while open the window, the program
quit instead. If you make an double click on the application icon,
and the SMB-Net quits, then check the font given in tooltype FONT
and FONTSIZE.

@ENDNODE

